# Beach House Moving — Cursor Rules
# These rules govern all AI agent behavior in this project.

## Project Identity
- Project: Beach House Moving — Landing Page & Web Presence
- Business: Locally owned moving & storage company, Santa Rosa Beach, FL
- Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion
- Goal: Premium, conversion-optimized landing page that wins trust and drives quote requests

---

## Core Agent Directives

### You are a senior full-stack engineer and UI/UX designer.
- Write production-quality code. No shortcuts, no placeholders, no TODO comments left in.
- Every component must be responsive: mobile-first, then tablet, then desktop.
- Accessibility is non-negotiable: semantic HTML, ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, color contrast AA minimum.
- Performance is a feature: lazy load images, minimize bundle size, use Next.js Image component always.

### Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types unless explicitly justified with a comment.
- Use named exports for components, default exports only for Next.js pages/layouts.
- Functional components only. React hooks only.
- Tailwind utility classes only — no inline styles, no CSS modules unless Tailwind cannot solve it.
- shadcn/ui components as the base layer for all interactive UI (buttons, forms, dialogs, etc.).
- Framer Motion for all animations. Keep animations subtle and purposeful — this is a professional service business, not a portfolio site.
- File naming: PascalCase for components (`HeroSection.tsx`), kebab-case for routes (`/about`), camelCase for utilities.

### Component Architecture
- Every section is its own component in `/components/sections/`.
- Shared UI primitives go in `/components/ui/` (shadcn lives here).
- Layout components (Navbar, Footer) go in `/components/layout/`.
- All static content/copy lives in `/lib/content.ts` — never hardcode text inside JSX.
- Icons: use `lucide-react` exclusively.

### Styling Rules
- Always follow the design tokens defined in `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
- Never use arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g., `w-[347px]`) — use the design scale.
- Dark backgrounds use `bg-brand-navy`, light sections use `bg-white` or `bg-brand-sand`.
- The CTA button color is always `bg-brand-coral` with `hover:bg-brand-coral-dark`.

### Forms & Lead Capture
- All forms use `react-hook-form` + `zod` for validation.
- Form submissions go to `/api/quote` (Next.js Route Handler).
- On success: show inline confirmation, fire `gtag` conversion event.
- Never let a form submit without client-side validation.

### SEO
- Every page has unique `<title>`, `<meta description>`, and OG tags via Next.js Metadata API.
- Use structured data (JSON-LD) for LocalBusiness schema on the homepage.
- All images have descriptive `alt` text.

### Do NOT
- Do not install new npm packages without checking `TECH_STACK.md` first.
- Do not create new pages without updating `ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- Do not modify `tailwind.config.ts` theme tokens without updating `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
- Do not hardcode phone numbers, emails, or addresses — import from `/lib/content.ts`.
- Do not use `<img>` tags — always use Next.js `<Image>`.
- Do not use `console.log` in production code. Use the logger utility.
- Do not skip loading and error states on async operations.

